---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import AVTeamCarousel from "../../components/AVTeamCarousel.astro";
import { avTeamHub, avTeamRoles } from "../../data/avTeam";

const APP_URL = "https://app.worshipmetrics.com";
const SITE_URL = "https://worshipmetrics.com";
const R2 = "https://pub-a4845709a76642e7943bcb8b80677531.r2.dev/main";
const HERO_IMAGE = `${R2}/homepage/new%20images/Worship%20Volunteers%20Working%20Together.jpg`;
const PANEL_IMAGE = `${R2}/Tech%20Manager/WorshipMetrics%20Tech%20Manager%20Web-UI%20Panels.jpg`;

const structuredData = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "WebPage",
  name: "Build Your AV Team",
  url: `${SITE_URL}/av-team`,
  description: avTeamHub.metaDescription,
  image: HERO_IMAGE,
};
---

<Layout
  title="Build Your AV Team"
  description={avTeamHub.metaDescription}
  canonical="/av-team"
  ogImage={HERO_IMAGE}
  structuredData={structuredData}
>
  <section class="bg-gradient-to-b from-indigo-50 via-white to-white px-4 py-20 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <div class="mx-auto grid max-w-6xl items-center gap-12 lg:grid-cols-[minmax(0,0.92fr)_minmax(0,1.08fr)]">
      <div>
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-indigo-600">AV Team</p>
        <h1 class="mt-4 text-4xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-slate-900 sm:text-5xl lg:text-6xl">{avTeamHub.heroHeading}</h1>
        <p class="mt-6 max-w-2xl text-lg leading-relaxed text-slate-600 sm:text-xl">{avTeamHub.heroSubheading}</p>
        <div class="mt-8 flex flex-col items-start gap-4 sm:flex-row sm:flex-wrap sm:items-center">
          <a href="#roles" class="btn-primary">See how it works</a>
          <a href="/discovery-call" class="btn-outline">Book a demo</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="overflow-hidden rounded-[1.75rem] border border-slate-200 bg-white shadow-[0_24px_60px_rgba(15,23,42,0.12)]">
        <img src={HERO_IMAGE} alt="Church AV team volunteers serving together" loading="eager" decoding="async" class="aspect-[16/10] w-full object-cover" />
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="roles" class="bg-white px-4 py-20 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-6xl">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl text-center">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-indigo-600">The seven roles</p>
        <h2 class="mt-3 text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight text-slate-900 sm:text-4xl">The shape of a real team.</h2>
        <p class="mt-4 text-base leading-relaxed text-slate-600 sm:text-lg">
          Most churches do not need seven experts overnight. They need a structure that can start with three or four volunteers and grow into something stronger over time. These seven roles give that structure to the church on day one.
        </p>
      </div>
      <AVTeamCarousel heading="Pick a role to see exactly what that volunteer does." />
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="bg-slate-50 px-4 py-20 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-6xl space-y-8">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl text-center">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-indigo-600">The problem every church media team hits</p>
        <h2 class="mt-3 text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight text-slate-900 sm:text-4xl">Most churches do not have an AV department. They have one person.</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="grid gap-6 lg:grid-cols-3">
        {[
          "When that one person gets sick, leaves, burns out, or graduates, the whole media ministry grinds to a halt.",
          "WorshipMetrics Pro fixes this at the structural level by giving the church defined roles instead of one overloaded operator.",
          "The result is not just better Sunday execution. It is a healthier team, a clearer training path, and a stronger ministry story.",
        ].map((body) => (
          <div class="rounded-[1.75rem] border border-slate-200 bg-white p-8 shadow-sm text-sm leading-relaxed text-slate-600">{body}</div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="bg-white px-4 py-20 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <div class="mx-auto grid max-w-6xl gap-12 lg:grid-cols-[minmax(0,1.02fr)_minmax(0,0.98fr)]">
      <div>
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-indigo-600">Why this changes everything</p>
        <h2 class="mt-3 text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight text-slate-900 sm:text-4xl">Young people stay in church when they have a role.</h2>
        <p class="mt-4 text-base leading-relaxed text-slate-600 sm:text-lg">
          A real AV team creates a place where teenagers and young adults are needed, not just welcomed. They get a title, a team, a skill to grow in, and a path to promotion over time.
        </p>
        <ul class="mt-8 space-y-3 text-sm text-slate-700 sm:text-base">
          {[
            "A place where they are needed, not just invited to attend",
            "A skill to master that builds pride and confidence",
            "A real team where contribution matters visibly every week",
            "A progression path from first seat to leadership",
          ].map((item) => (
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3"><span class="mt-2 h-2.5 w-2.5 flex-shrink-0 rounded-full bg-indigo-500"></span><span>{item}</span></li>
          ))}
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="overflow-hidden rounded-[1.75rem] border border-slate-200 bg-white shadow-sm">
        <img src={PANEL_IMAGE} alt="Volunteer-friendly AV role panels in WorshipMetrics" loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="aspect-[16/10] w-full object-cover" />
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="bg-slate-50 px-4 py-20 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-6xl">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl text-center">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-indigo-600">What WorshipMetrics Pro gives you</p>
        <h2 class="mt-3 text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight text-slate-900 sm:text-4xl">A prebuilt team structure, not just a better control surface.</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="mt-10 grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-2 xl:grid-cols-4">
        {[
          "A purpose-built control panel for each volunteer role",
          "Documentation baked into the buttons so volunteers can contribute quickly",
          "Training-friendly workflows that make onboarding easier",
          "A clear path to promote into the next seat as the team grows",
        ].map((item) => (
          <div class="rounded-[1.5rem] border border-slate-200 bg-white p-6 text-sm leading-relaxed text-slate-600 shadow-sm">{item}</div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="bg-white px-4 py-20 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-6xl">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl text-center">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-indigo-600">Roles at a glance</p>
        <h2 class="mt-3 text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight text-slate-900 sm:text-4xl">Start with three or four. Grow into all seven.</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="mt-10 overflow-hidden rounded-[2rem] border border-slate-200 bg-white shadow-sm">
        <table class="w-full text-sm">
          <thead class="bg-slate-50 text-left">
            <tr>
              <th class="px-6 py-4 font-semibold text-slate-700">Role</th>
              <th class="px-6 py-4 font-semibold text-slate-700">What they own</th>
              <th class="px-6 py-4 font-semibold text-slate-700">Typical age</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody class="divide-y divide-slate-200 bg-white">
            {avTeamRoles.map((role) => (
              <tr>
                <td class="px-6 py-4 font-semibold text-slate-900"><a href={`/av-team/${role.slug}`} class="hover:text-indigo-600">{role.title}</a></td>
                <td class="px-6 py-4 text-slate-600">{role.oneLine}</td>
                <td class="px-6 py-4 text-slate-600">{role.typicalAge}</td>
              </tr>
            ))}
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="bg-slate-950 px-4 py-20 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-6xl rounded-[2rem] border border-white/10 bg-white/5 p-8 shadow-2xl sm:p-12">
      <div class="grid gap-10 lg:grid-cols-[minmax(0,1fr)_minmax(0,0.95fr)]">
        <div>
          <p class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-indigo-300">A note to the tech manager</p>
          <h2 class="mt-3 text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight text-white sm:text-4xl">You do not need to replace your whole room to build a real team.</h2>
          <p class="mt-4 text-base leading-relaxed text-slate-300 sm:text-lg">
            The point of this system is not to force a giant hardware reset. It is to map role-friendly controls onto the gear and software your church already uses so more people can serve without everything becoming harder.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="space-y-4">
          {[
            "Bring your existing gear, your production computer, and your Wi-Fi.",
            "Get role-specific control panels configured for the systems your church already owns.",
            "Let volunteers use laptops, phones, or WorshipMetrics Tablets instead of buying dedicated control surfaces for every seat.",
          ].map((item) => (
            <div class="rounded-2xl border border-white/10 bg-white/5 p-4 text-sm leading-relaxed text-slate-200">{item}</div>
          ))}
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="bg-white px-4 py-20 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-6xl">
      <AVTeamCarousel heading="Ready to start? Pick a role." />
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="bg-indigo-600 px-4 py-20 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl text-center">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight text-white sm:text-4xl">Build a team your church can grow into.</h2>
      <p class="mx-auto mt-4 max-w-3xl text-base leading-relaxed text-indigo-100 sm:text-lg">
        Start with the roles you need now, then grow the team as more volunteers find their place.
      </p>
      <div class="mt-8 flex flex-col items-center justify-center gap-4 sm:flex-row sm:flex-wrap">
        <a href={`${APP_URL}/sign-up`} class="btn-primary" style="background:#fff;color:#4361ee;box-shadow:0 10px 30px rgba(15,23,42,0.18);">Get started free</a>
        <a href="/discovery-call" class="btn-outline" style="border-color:rgba(255,255,255,0.35);color:#fff;">Book a demo</a>
        <a href="/av-club" class="btn-outline" style="border-color:rgba(255,255,255,0.35);color:#fff;">See the AV Club vision</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
